&quot;When We Were Beautiful&quot; is a song by American band Bon Jovi. It was originally written by Jon Bon Jovi, Richie Sambora and Billy Falcon for a Bon Jovi greatest hits collection that got shelved. It was released as an iTunes only promo single from The Circle in the US. It became available as a digital download from the US iTunes store on October 26, 2009. The song was released for download to coincide with Bon Jovi documentary &quot;When We Were Beautiful&quot; on Showtime. The song has since been released as the third official single from the album with the music video being released on May 24, 2010.

The music video was shot with the band performing live; and the vocals are taken from this show. The video focuses predominantly on Jon Bon Jovi singing, although the rest of the band can also be seen.

The song talks about a bleak world that used to be more than what it has become, and the narrator wishes to find what made that better world work, so he may then try to make his world a better place. The song's lyrics are very deeply written without being too hard to interpret.

The Circle is the title of the eleventh studio album by rock band Bon Jovi. Produced by John Shanks, the album was released November 10, 2009, with the new single &quot;We Weren't Born to Follow&quot; premiering on radio August 17. The album was released in Germany and Ireland on October 30, 2009. The album debuted at number 1 in several countries, including the U.S., where it sold 163,000 copies in its first week debuting at number 1 on the Billboard 200. This gives them their fourth number 1 album after their 2007 effort, Lost Highway.

